## 3. Commands to test

No experts present (default fallback for every mode):
```bash
python -c "
from controllers.mission_manager import MissionManager
from sim.flight_modes import FlightMode
mm = MissionManager().load()
print('experts registered:', list(mm._experts.keys()))
for mode in FlightMode:
    print(mode.name, '-> default' if mm.get_active_expert(mode) is mm._default_expert else '-> EXPERT')
"
```

With one expert present:
```bash
cp models/best_success.zip models/experts/stabilize.zip
python -c "
from controllers.mission_manager import MissionManager
from sim.flight_modes import FlightMode
mm = MissionManager().load()
print('experts registered:', list(mm._experts.keys()))
for mode in FlightMode:
    print(mode.name, '-> default' if mm.get_active_expert(mode) is mm._default_expert else '-> EXPERT')
"
rm models/experts/stabilize.zip
```

I ran both above using the project's `venv`.

